<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<task id="025" project="spaarkeai-compose-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>BFF — Register Compose services + map endpoint group in Program.cs</title>
    <phase>Phase 2: BFF Endpoints + Services</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>3</estimated-hours>
    <tags>bff-api, backend, di, config</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Task tags include 'bff-api' (code implementation)</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Mutates Program.cs (shared file); must run after endpoints (024) exist.</parallel-reason>
    <dependencies>024</dependencies>
    <blocks>027</blocks>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Wire the three Compose services + endpoints into `Program.cs` via a focused `AddComposeModule()` DI extension and a `MapComposeEndpoints()` route registration. Registrations MUST be unconditional (no feature flag) to match endpoints' unconditional mapping (avoids RB-T028 asymmetric-registration anti-pattern per bff-extensions.md §F.1). Follow ADR-010 DI minimalism — one focused `Add{Feature}Module()` extension, not a flat blob in `Program.cs`.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior .NET developer expert in ASP.NET Core DI, the Spaarke BFF feature-module convention (per ADR-010), and the bff-extensions.md asymmetric-registration anti-pattern. Comfortable making targeted, additive `Program.cs` edits.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `Program.cs` calls `builder.Services.AddComposeModule()` (unconditional) and `app.MapComposeEndpoints()` (unconditional). The new `Infrastructure/Modules/ComposeModule.cs` (or similar location matching existing module convention) registers `IComposeService`, `IComposeDocumentService`, `IComposeSessionService` as scoped services. BFF builds clean; smoke-test endpoints respond.
  </prompt>

  <context>
    <background>
      bff-extensions.md §C #5 mandates "register through a `Map{Feature}Endpoints` extension method," and §F.1 codifies the unconditional-DI/unconditional-mapping rule from RB-T028-03/04/05/06. This task wires both. ADR-010 + plan.md §3 Key Technical Decisions reinforce: feature-module DI, not a flat blob.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Program.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/Modules/ComposeModule.cs (NEW)</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">DI minimalism — register through focused `AddComposeModule()` extension, NOT a flat blob of registrations in `Program.cs`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">Compose services must register without pulling AI internals into their dependency graph. Verify by static-scan: no `IOpenAiClient` / `IPlaybookService` in the three Compose service constructors (only PublicContracts facade types if AI is needed — and only the endpoint, not the services, is allowed to inject those).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Registrations MUST be unconditional (no `if (flag)` block). Endpoints map unconditionally in task 024; DI MUST match (bff-extensions.md §F.1).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Service lifetimes: `Scoped` for IComposeService / IComposeDocumentService / IComposeSessionService (match BFF convention — per-request scope inherits auth context).</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <justification>
    <existing>`src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Program.cs` and existing feature-module extensions under `Infrastructure/Modules/` are the established convention. No existing module bundles upload+load+save+promote+session-binding for an editor host.</existing>
    <extension>Yes for `Program.cs` (two new lines added — pure extension). New for `ComposeModule.cs` because Compose is a discrete feature surface per the spec; matches ADR-010 feature-module convention.</extension>
    <cost-of-doing-nothing>FR-21 endpoints throw at runtime — services are not in DI; HTTP requests would fail with `InvalidOperationException` on first hit.</cost-of-doing-nothing>
  </justification>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarkeai-compose-r1/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarkeai-compose-r1/plan.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarkeai-compose-r1/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/PublicContracts/ConsumerTypes.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/PublicContracts/ConsumerRoutingService.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/ChatSessionManager.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/FileAccessEndpoints.cs</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context check + load knowledge">Verify context &lt; 70%. Load Program.cs, an existing `*Module.cs` for convention, and bff-extensions.md §§A,C,F.1.</step>
    <step order="1" name="Create ComposeModule">Create `Infrastructure/Modules/ComposeModule.cs` with `public static IServiceCollection AddComposeModule(this IServiceCollection services)`. Register: `AddScoped&lt;IComposeService, ComposeService&gt;()`, `AddScoped&lt;IComposeDocumentService, ComposeDocumentService&gt;()`, `AddScoped&lt;IComposeSessionService, ComposeSessionService&gt;()`. Return services.</step>
    <step order="2" name="Wire Program.cs DI">Add `builder.Services.AddComposeModule();` at the appropriate position in `Program.cs` (near other feature-module registrations). Unconditional — no `if (flag)` wrapper.</step>
    <step order="3" name="Wire Program.cs endpoint mapping">Add `app.MapComposeEndpoints();` at the appropriate position (with other `Map*Endpoints` calls). Unconditional.</step>
    <step order="4" name="Static-scan for AI-internal leakage">Per bff-extensions.md §F.1 recipe, grep Compose service constructors for `IOpenAiClient` / `IPlaybookService` / direct AI-internal types. None permitted.</step>
    <step order="5" name="Build BFF">`dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` — must be clean.</step>
    <step order="6" name="Smoke-run host">Start the BFF host locally (or via dotnet run) and verify the host boots without DI-resolution errors. Hit an unauthenticated endpoint and confirm 401 (verifies endpoints are mapped + auth works).</step>
    <step order="7" name="Measure publish-size impact">`dotnet publish -c Release src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/`; report compressed delta vs ~45.65 MB baseline (expect ≤+0.05 MB — pure DI wiring).</step>
    <step order="8" name="CVE check + update TASK-INDEX">`dotnet list package --vulnerable --include-transitive` — must show no new HIGH-severity CVE. Update `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: change task 025 status to ✅. Reset `current-task.md`.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="dotnet">Build, run, publish, CVE scan</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/Modules/ComposeModule.cs</output>
